\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddison_Keeney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddison_Keeney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Canoe sprinters Tom Green and Jean van der Westhuyzen got bronze.\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 827, \"end\": 836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Green\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8919318868079135e-20, \"text\": \"Tom Green\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Green\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Green\"}, {\"begin\": 841, \"end\": 864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_van_der_Westhuyzen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jean van der Westhuyzen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_van_der_Westhuyzen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_van_der_Westhuyzen\"}, {\"begin\": 841, \"end\": 864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_van_der_Westhuyzen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jean van der Westhuyzen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_van_der_Westhuyzen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_van_der_Westhuyzen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This brings Australia to a total of 48 medals so far: 18 gold, 16 silver and 14 bronze.\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 965, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 890, \"end\": 899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9998319695561542, \"rank\": 0.00016212530121755998, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Matt Richardson has finished runner-up to Dutch star Harrie Lavreysen in the track cycling sprint.\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 1065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 967, \"end\": 982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matt Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 1009, \"end\": 1014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9992169443819031, \"rank\": 0.0006121614295968341, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 1020, \"end\": 1036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Harrie Lavreysen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was Richardson's first individual Olympic medal, after he won bronze earlier this week in the team sprint.\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1074, \"end\": 1084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999999302131097, \"rank\": 6.978681764324189e-08, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I put my best foot forward, I did not leave anything out on the track.\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He's (Lavreysen) one of the greatest sprinters we have ever seen on this planet,\\\" Richardson said.\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1348, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1332, \"end\": 1342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999999302131097, \"rank\": 6.978681764324189e-08, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am extremely proud of the silver.\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1386, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have bronze and silver - there is one more to collect and that's what we will try to do in the keirin.\\\"\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1492, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He and Matt Glaetzer will ride the opening keirin heats on Saturday.\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1537, \"end\": 1543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.142309925651906e-62, \"text\": \"keirin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maddison Keeney has become the first Australian diver ever to win an individual Olympic 3m springboard medal - a glorious silver - in Paris.\", \"from\": 1564, \"to\": 1704, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1564, \"end\": 1579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddison_Keeney\", \"score\": 0.9999999320498342, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Maddison Keeney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddison_Keeney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddison_Keeney\"}, {\"begin\": 1601, \"end\": 1611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999997847058016, \"rank\": 2.1526800292961532e-07, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 1698, \"end\": 1703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0865858050593392e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 28-year-old from Perth received her biggest medal yet on the podium from one her heroes, Oscar-winning actress and IOC member Michelle Yeoh.\", \"from\": 1706, \"to\": 1850, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1727, \"end\": 1732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perth\", \"score\": 0.9999999953306542, \"rank\": 4.552507702580042e-09, \"text\": \"Perth\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perth\"}, {\"begin\": 1825, \"end\": 1835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"IOC member\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1836, \"end\": 1844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"score\": 0.9999991082312928, \"rank\": 8.894845599341184e-07, \"text\": \"Michelle\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Winner of a springboard synchro bronze in 2016, she had delivered her best ever performance under the utmost pressure on Friday, beaten only by another of the seemingly invincible Chinese divers, Chen Yiwen.\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 2059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2032, \"end\": 2039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9876855532696528, \"rank\": 0.01234373593580668, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2048, \"end\": 2058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Yiwen\", \"score\": 0.9999955748669574, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chen Yiwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Yiwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Yiwen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She scored 343.10 from her five-dive program as Chen proved a runaway winner with 376.00.\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2109, \"end\": 2113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\", \"score\": 0.7715821190491332, \"rank\": 0.29603624380519905, \"text\": \"Chen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Shui-bian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was very nervous today,\\\" she revealed.\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2193, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I have been working really close with my psych for the last 10 years.\\\"\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2269, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Many times my legs have buckled from under me, but going through all those experiences, falling off the board, it's kind of made me who I am today.\", \"from\": 2271, \"to\": 2419, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel like I have been forged in fire.\\\"\", \"from\": 2420, \"to\": 2460, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Australian paddlers Tom Green and Jean van der Westhuyzen will leave Paris with a bronze, unable to repeat their Olympic heroics in the men's K2 event.\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2613, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2462, \"end\": 2472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999997847058016, \"rank\": 2.1526800292961532e-07, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 2482, \"end\": 2491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Green\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8919318868079135e-20, \"text\": \"Tom Green\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Green\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Green\"}, {\"begin\": 2496, \"end\": 2519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_van_der_Westhuyzen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jean van der Westhuyzen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_van_der_Westhuyzen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_van_der_Westhuyzen\"}, {\"begin\": 2496, \"end\": 2519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_van_der_Westhuyzen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jean van der Westhuyzen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_van_der_Westhuyzen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_van_der_Westhuyzen\"}, {\"begin\": 2531, \"end\": 2536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0865858050593392e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite smashing a 20-year-old Olympic record in the semi-final earlier on Friday at the Vaires-sur-Marne Nautical Stadium, Green and van der Westhuyzen could not catch Germany's Max Lemke and Jacob Schopf in the medal race and crossed the line third.\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2866, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2704, \"end\": 2720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.250425072495666e-19, \"text\": \"Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vaires-sur-Marne\"}, {\"begin\": 2794, \"end\": 2803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Lemke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Max Lemke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Lemke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Lemke\"}, {\"begin\": 2808, \"end\": 2820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacob_Schopf\", \"score\": 0.9999732867184433, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jacob Schopf\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacob_Schopf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacob_Schopf\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hungary's Sandor Totka and Bence Nadas won silver.\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 2918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2868, \"end\": 2875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9998490217641398, \"rank\": 0.00015100103124848636, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The pair won the title in Tokyo, however the 1000m event was replaced by a 500m race for the 2024 Games.\", \"from\": 2920, \"to\": 3024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2946, \"end\": 2951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9990630332949402, \"rank\": 0.0009378454350779445, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We would have loved to come here and get the gold again but we will live to fight another day and coming back home with the dirty gold is not too bad,\\\" said 25-year-old van der Westhuyzen.\", \"from\": 3026, \"to\": 3215, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif has claimed gold at the Paris Olympics, emerging as a champion from a tumultuous run which included hugescrutiny over her eligibility.\", \"from\": 3217, \"to\": 3358, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif beat Yang Liu of China 5-0 in the final of the women's welterweight division, wrapping up the best series of fights of her boxing career.\", \"from\": 3360, \"to\": 3504, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3372, \"end\": 3380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\", \"score\": 0.9999966834675861, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yang Liu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\"}, {\"begin\": 3384, \"end\": 3389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9950751080671661, \"rank\": 0.0049470459193256475, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's huge Algerian community embraced Khelif, but outside of the competition venues she faced extraordinary levels of criticism, which thrust her into a larger divide over changing attitudes toward gender identity and regulations in sports.\", \"from\": 3506, \"to\": 3750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3506, \"end\": 3512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.8074673494444204, \"rank\": 0.19806983011645343, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif said the level of abuse \\\"harms human dignity,\\\" calling for an end to bullying athletes.\", \"from\": 3752, \"to\": 3846, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She also said a gold medal would be \\\"the best response\\\" to the backlash against her.\", \"from\": 3847, \"to\": 3931, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif's gold medal is Algeria's first in women's boxing.\", \"from\": 3933, \"to\": 3990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3956, \"end\": 3963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.7798643682466567, \"rank\": 0.2822742525208043, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is only the nation's second boxing gold medalist, joining Hocine Soltani (1996).\", \"from\": 3991, \"to\": 4075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4053, \"end\": 4067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hocine_Soltani\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hocine Soltani\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hocine_Soltani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hocine_Soltani\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first Olympic breakers took the stage this Friday at Place de la Concorde, where even rapper Snoop Dogg showed off a few of his own moves before opening the event.\", \"from\": 4077, \"to\": 4244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4134, \"end\": 4154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0199209406371665e-14, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}, {\"begin\": 4174, \"end\": 4184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australian Rachael Gunn, aka Raygun, made history as one of the country's first Olympic breakers, but she bowed out without firing a shot.\", \"from\": 4246, \"to\": 4384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4246, \"end\": 4256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.99999978