g/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4444, \"end\": 4454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999997847058016, \"rank\": 2.1526800292961532e-07, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 4533, \"end\": 4539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9673790826890413, \"rank\": 0.031383505112778244, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The athletes were judged on creativity, personality, technique, variety, musicality and vocabulary, which is the variation and quantity of moves.\", \"from\": 4555, \"to\": 4700, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia's 16-year-old B-boy Jeff Dunne, known as 'J Attack', will line up in the male competition on Saturday.\", \"from\": 4702, \"to\": 4814, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4702, \"end\": 4711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9998319695561542, \"rank\": 0.00016212530121755998, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 4732, \"end\": 4742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeff_Dunne\", \"score\": 0.9999935803067791, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeff Dunne\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeff_Dunne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeff_Dunne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Manizha Talash, a member of the refugee Olympic team at the Paris Games, was disqualified after displaying the words \\\"Free Afghan Women\\\" on her cape during her breaking routine in the competition's pre-qualifiers on Friday.\", \"from\": 4816, \"to\": 5039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4816, \"end\": 4823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.